@chapter The Internal Representation
The backbone of synopsis is an Internal Representation of the parsed source code.
This is essentially a set of different representations, such as an Abstract Semantic Graph,
a Symbol Table, Parse Tree, etc.
These are designed to be (mostly) language-agnostic, so they can be used with multiple
languages.

This chapter describes the most important common building blocks of the Internal 
Representation.
